        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2651687750" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1330310479567296193">Absolutely loved this book about a biologist living amongst the wolves for a while in the Arctic. Mr Mowat has a great way of writing and is actually really funny. I&apos;d even recommend this to non-biologists or people not interested in wolves, you&apos;ll love them after this book. They are seriously misunderstood animals, very smart and not as violent as most people think. It all depends on the situation, and it is true that loads of their habitat is taken by humans. <br/><br/>Recently a few wolves have been sp</span>
  <span id="freeText1330310479567296193" style="display:none">Absolutely loved this book about a biologist living amongst the wolves for a while in the Arctic. Mr Mowat has a great way of writing and is actually really funny. I'd even recommend this to non-biologists or people not interested in wolves, you'll love them after this book. They are seriously misunderstood animals, very smart and not as violent as most people think. It all depends on the situation, and it is true that loads of their habitat is taken by humans. <br /><br />Recently a few wolves have been spotted in the Netherlands, after about seventy years without them, and ofcourse the country is in an uproar. I wish everyone would read this book to understand that this does not have to be a problem.<br /><br />I realise that this is a fictional book, as in, it's embellished to give a positive impression of wolves and leaves out some of the more predatory instincts of the animals. I do believe though that wolves want nothing to do with humans when they have everything they need (space, food, rest). <br /><br />Highly enjoyable!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1330310479567296193" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


